The Caretaker Publicity Secretary of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Delta State Sylvester Imonina (Esq.) has resigned from the party. Imonina turned in his resignation Tuesday in a letter addressed to the State’s party chairman. The letter dated January 18, 2022, reads: “Due to the state of affairs of All Progressives Congress, Delta State chapter, I, Ogheneluemu Sylvester Imonina, herein resign my membership of the party and my position as the acting State Publicity Secretary.   Time has come to choose wisely     Osun 2022: Adeleke family bickers over PDP ticket     2023 election not a do or die affair – Buni   “I want to use this opportunity to thank the leaders of my Ward, LGA, APC Isoko nation and members of the party across the state for the support given to me while I contributed my quota to the development of the party.” - Advertisement - He also thanked all who stood by him throughout his political sojourn.